  "methodology_note": "Benchmark numbers aggregated from vendor model cards, lmarena.ai, artificialanalysis.ai, HuggingFace Open LLM Leaderboard, the Aider leaderboard, and SWE-bench Verified. Pricing is per 1M tokens in USD on each provider's first-party API. Open-weights pricing reflects the typical Together / Fireworks / OpenRouter rate. Cells set to null indicate the vendor has not published that benchmark or pricing tier. Models superseded by a newer same-vendor entry are retained when still in active use; truly stagnant lines are removed. Claude Fable 5 (added 2026-06-10) launched without a full public benchmark card; its scores are positioned estimates consistent with Anthropic's 'most intelligent model, a new tier above Opus' framing and will be replaced with published figures when available. Kimi K2.7-Code (added 2026-06-14) shipped only Moonshot's proprietary coding benchmarks at launch; its public-benchmark cells are conservative estimates anchored to the published Kimi K2.6 predecessor (SWE-bench Verified 80.2, MMLU-Pro 87.1) and to peer open coders, and will be replaced with third-party figures when available. GLM-5.2 (added 2026-06-21) is Zhipu AI's open-weights coding flagship; its vendor card published long-horizon coding benchmarks (SWE-bench Pro 62.1, FrontierSWE 74.4, MCP-Atlas 77.0) but not the standard public set. Its swe_bench cell carries the vendor's published SWE-bench Pro 62.1, matching how the GLM-5.1 predecessor row was recorded; the remaining cells are conservative estimates anchored to GLM-5.1 (MMLU-Pro 82.0, GPQA 72.0, HumanEval 90.0, MATH-500 92.0, Aider 64.0, tau-bench 56.0), nudged up on coding/agentic axes consistent with a coding-first refresh, and will be replaced with third-party figures when available. Update cadence: monthly.",
